value:
First draft of the recitative and uncompleted aria of the oratorio Joseph and his brethren, Part I, Scene IV, HWV 59 Anhang (9.), and a probably unrelated minuet for violin and continuo.
Two leaves probably removed from the holograph (R.M. 20.e.10) during course of composition.
Holograph manuscript in ink.
With scribbled annotations in right hand margin of page 21:  "comme/ je ne", "demn" "Sans" "aucun" : see also pp. 66 and 79.
Watermark: "LVG" below fleur de lis over Strasbourg bend; countermark: "IV" (Burrows C80)

Contents:
[p. 21] Whence this unwonted ardour in my breast : [recitative for S (Asenath), bc] -- [p. 21-23] I feel a spreading flame : [aria for S, vl1, vl2, vla, b] -- [p. 24] Menuet [for treble (violin) and bass in D major, HWV 420 : uncompleted first draft of melody written on lines 1 & 3, with complete minuet on lines 5-8]
